OL,3,CLife sentence given to 80 year old man
OL,4,Cfor murdering his neighbour
OL,6,FHowever, he came back with a knife and
OL,7,Fstabbed John Jones, causing a fatal
OL,8,Finjury.
OL,10,FPeter Kindell was arrested shortly
OL,11,Fafterwards, and made no comment to
OL,12,Fmost questions asked by police. In
OL,13,Fcourt, he claimed he killed Mr Jones
OL,14,Fdue to diminished responsibility.
OL,16,FThe prosecution did not accept his
OL,17,Fdefence, and the 80-year old was given
OL,18,Fa mandatory life sentence, with a
OL,19,Fminimum term of 22 years.
